<seg id="313">"In the specific case of the Santarém tower, the annual deficit is around a half a ton of carbon per hectare", says Paulo Artaxo, from the Physics Institute of the University of Sao Paulo, one of the LBA coordinators.</seg>
<seg id="314">The sea and the forest</seg>
<seg id="315">For Dr. Wofsy, the cause of the unprecedented negative balance in the flow of carbon dioxide measured at the tower in Santarém is related to the effects on the regional climate brought about during the last decade by successive El Niños, the abnormal warming of the superficial waters of the South Pacific that alters the indices of rainfall and temperature in several spots of the globe.</seg>
