<seg id="368">Although almost imperceptible at room temperature, vacuum acts in a way that is similar to a magneticfield, resulting from the action of a common magnet, and manages to draw together two neutral metallic plates, in parallel andkept at a temperature close to absolute zero (-273o Celsius), as has already been demonstrated experimentally -- it is theCasimir force, identified in 1954.</seg>
